org.ecemgroup.sharevitalsigns.library

Class ShareVitalSigns

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ecemgroup.sharevitalsigns.library.ShareVitalSigns

  • public class ShareVitalSigns
extends java.lang.Object
    ShareVitalSigns Class Library class which provides functions for sending vital signs and other medical data between android applications. The library can be used by a vital sign provider (e.g. that records this from a sensor) or a vital sign receiver (that displays or process this vital sign further). Check ShareVitalSignsDemoReceiver for an example of a receiver Check ShareVitalSignsDemoSender for an example of a provider Check RRate for an example of a provider that records respiratory rate with tapping on the screen. the library essentially uses Intents. More on intents check the Android developer website: http://developer.android.com/guide/components/intents-filters.html VitalSigns currently supported: HR: Heart Rate beats/min RR: Respiratory Rate breaths/min TEMP: Temperature deg Celcius SPO2: Oxygen saturation % BP_SYS: Blood pressure (Sys ) mmHg BP_DIA: Blood pressure (Sys ) mmHg Combinations: BP: Blood pressure (Sys & Dia) mmHg & mmHg PO: Pulse oximetry (HR & SPO2) beats/min & %
    Version:
    0.1.0
    Author:
    Walter Karlen (walter.karlen@ieee.org)
